[{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = GeomOpt","category":"page"},{"location":"#GeomOpt","page":"Home","title":"GeomOpt","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Documentation for GeomOpt.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Modules = [GeomOpt]","category":"page"},{"location":"#GeomOpt.cartesian_to_fractional-Tuple{AtomsBase.AbstractSystem, AbstractVector{<:AbstractVector{<:Union{Unitful.Quantity{T, 𝐋, U}, Unitful.Level{L, S, Unitful.Quantity{T, 𝐋, U}} where {L, S}} where {T, U}}}}","page":"Home","title":"GeomOpt.cartesian_to_fractional","text":"cartesian_to_fractional(system::AbstractSystem, positions::AbstractVector{<:AbstractVector{<:Real}})\n\nGiven a list of cartesian coordinates, convert them to fractional.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#GeomOpt.clamp_atoms-Tuple{AtomsBase.AbstractSystem, Union{Nothing, AbstractVector{<:Integer}}}","page":"Home","title":"GeomOpt.clamp_atoms","text":"Clamp given atoms if the system. Clamped atoms are fixed and their positions  will not be optimized. The atoms to be clamped should be given as a list of  indies corresponding to their positions in system.particles.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#GeomOpt.construct_optimization_function-Tuple{AtomsBase.AbstractSystem, Any}","page":"Home","title":"GeomOpt.construct_optimization_function","text":"By default we work in cartesian coordinaes.\nNote that internally, when optimizing the cartesian positions, atomic units \nare used.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#GeomOpt.fractional_to_cartesian-Tuple{AtomsBase.AbstractSystem, AbstractVector{<:AbstractVector{<:Real}}}","page":"Home","title":"GeomOpt.fractional_to_cartesian","text":"fractional_to_cartesian(system::AbstractSystem, positions::AbstractVector{<:AbstractVector{<:Real}})\n\nGiven a list of fractional coordinates, convert them to cartesian.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#GeomOpt.get_optimizable_mask-Tuple{AtomsBase.AbstractSystem}","page":"Home","title":"GeomOpt.get_optimizable_mask","text":"get_optimizable_mask(system::AbstractSystem) -> AbstractVector{<:Bool}\n\nReturns the optimizable mask of the system (see documentation for set_optimizable_mask.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#GeomOpt.mask_vector_list-Tuple{AbstractVector{<:AbstractVector}, AbstractVector{<:Bool}}","page":"Home","title":"GeomOpt.mask_vector_list","text":"Given a list of vectors and a mask, return the masked version in a one-dimensional list. This is used to concatenate the forces returned in the scfres into a single list,  that can be used by the optimizer.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#GeomOpt.set_optimizable_mask-Tuple{AtomsBase.AbstractSystem, AbstractVector{<:Bool}}","page":"Home","title":"GeomOpt.set_optimizable_mask","text":"set_optimizable_mask(system::AbstractSystem, mask::AbstractVector{<:Bool})\n\nSets the mask defining which coordinates of the system can be optimized.  The mask is a vector of booleans, specifying which of the atoms can be optimized.\n\nBy default (when no mask is specified), all particles are assumed optimizable.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#GeomOpt.update_optimizable_coordinates-Union{Tuple{L}, Tuple{AtomsBase.AbstractSystem, AbstractVector{<:L}}} where L<:(Union{Unitful.Quantity{T, 𝐋, U}, Unitful.Level{L, S, Unitful.Quantity{T, 𝐋, U}} where {L, S}} where {T, U})","page":"Home","title":"GeomOpt.update_optimizable_coordinates","text":"update_optimizable_coordinates(system::AbstractSystem, positions::Vector{<:AbstractVector{<:L}}) where {L <: Unitful.Length}\n\nCreates a new system based on system with the optimizable coordinates are updated to the ones provided (in the order in which they appear in system.particles), cartesian coordinates version..\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#GeomOpt.update_positions-Union{Tuple{L}, Tuple{AtomsBase.AbstractSystem, AbstractVector{<:AbstractVector{L}}}} where L<:(Union{Unitful.Quantity{T, 𝐋, U}, Unitful.Level{L, S, Unitful.Quantity{T, 𝐋, U}} where {L, S}} where {T, U})","page":"Home","title":"GeomOpt.update_positions","text":"update_postions(system::AbstractSystem, positions::Vector{<:AbstractVector{<:Real}}) where {L <: Unitful.Length}\n\nCreates a new system based on system but with atoms positions updated to the ones specified in positions,  using cartesian coordinates.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"}]
